            "body": "> Thanks for looking into this. I guess this is different than #37454 which also is related to `didOpen` ? Does that PR have any implications for this one ?\r\n\r\nAfter looking at #37454 I can see a potential conflict. My guard is too broad it blocks any didopen for a buffer that already had one, which would incorrectly block the rename case where the uri changes but the bufnr stays the same. The fix is straightforward: key the guard by uri instead of bufnr. I'll implement that.",
