            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "To me this seems a bit strange because `Client:on_attach` and with it `_text_document_did_open_handler` is already guarded by `attached_buffers` (except for the on_reload case).\r\n\r\nAdding a second state map to guard it a second time feels off. Can you double check why the existing guards aren't sufficient for the given case?",
